<p>One of the reviews on the
<a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/redirect?tag=nedbatchelder-20&amp;path=tg%2Fdetail%2F-%2FB0000E3BT9%2Fqid%3D1103508237%2Fsr%3D8-3%2Fref%3Dsr_8_xs_ap_i3_xgl21%3Fv%3Dglance%26s%3Dtoys%26n%3D507846">i-top page at amazon</a>
describes extra modes that include a compass mode: the top displays N/E/S/W on top, acting as a compass.
I thought this was one of the coolest toys I'd seen in a while.
Also: the center spindle folds into the body of the top, leaving it with a sleek UFO profile.
E-bay is displaying listings for a new i-top Pro which can do even more.  I want one.
</p>

